    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-03-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-12-22T17:07:36Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Save America's Ports Act of 2006 - Prohibits, for a two-year period, the entering into a contract for the operation of a seaport or other point of entry into the United States if a party to such contract is or would be: (1) a government that has repeatedly provided support for acts of international terrorism; (2) a foreign terrorist organization; (3) a foreign person who has committed, or poses a significant risk of committing, acts of terrorism; or (4) an entity that is owned or controlled by such a government, organization, or person.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
